<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Sunday, March 7, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Susan Leh at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   DAVIS-TEACHERS (Sacramento) -- Critics fear sweeping plans to
overhaul California's educational system put on the legislative
fast track by Gov. Gray Davis are being watered down to appease to
cut teacher accountability, since teacher unions were among Davis'
biggest supporters in the last election. By Terri Hardy. (Will move
in the ``n'' state and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   MCCARTHY-COLUMN (Los Angeles) -- A former high school
cheerleader forced to leave school when her epilepsy became too
much, and who was then kicked off the sidelines at the homecoming
game because she wasn't a student, hasn't let adversity stop her
from dreaming. A recent operation and gutsy determination have her
on the road to completing her senior year. By Dennis McCarthy.
(Will move in the ``n'' state and ``a'' national news files, and
the ``k'' editorial file.)
</P>
