A0148 &Cx1f; tad-z
u l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-NEWUNIVERSAL-DISNEY07     03-06 0454
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NEWUNIVERSAL-DISNEY07-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Universal, Disney vie for summer supremacy
 &HT;    By Paul Lomartire
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Everyone worth their mouse ears at
Disney World knows that this summer will belong to crosstown
competitor Universal Studios.
</P>
<P>
   So both Disney and Universal are gearing up for the summer with
new additions. Let the games, and fun, begin!
</P>
<P>
   Don't eat until AFTER you try these thrill rides.
</P>
<P>
   In May, Universal opens a $2 billion expansion that includes a
22-ride theme park called Islands of Adventure. And while Disney
has more of almost every-theme-park-thing, it's lacking thrill
rides.
</P>
<P>
   Space Mountain and Big Thunder Mountain are fun, sure _ when
you're 10. Disney will open a coaster at Disney-MGM Studios in
June, but Universal tops that with two new monster coasters.
</P>
<P>
   Universal's ready to go with two monster roller coasters.
</P>
<P>
   The Incredible Hulk Coaster has 100-foot loops and a top speed
of nearly 60 mph. The Dueling Dragons roller coaster features
tracks that also take speeding riders up to 60 mph.
</P>
<P>
   The two roller coasters have three near misses, coming within 12
inches of each other.
</P>
<P>
   Another hotly anticipated Universal ride is the Adventures of
Spider-Man, combining a ride with filmed 3-D action, live actors
and special effects.
</P>
<P>
   The 110-acre Islands of Adventure is made up of five sections.
Seuss Landing and Toon Lagoon will appeal to elementary-age kids
while their older brothers and sisters will head to thrill
ride-filled Marvel Super Hero Island and The Lost Continent.
</P>
<P>
   Jurassic Park is an animatronic-filled area based on the Steven
Spielberg film and featuring an interactive water ride that
involves five-story dinosaurs and an 84-foot plunge.
</P>
<P>
   Why go all the way to Portofino, Italy, when you can go to a
sort-of-exact replica at Universal? The 750-room Portofino Bay,
which opens this summer, has a spa and eight themed restaurants and
lounges arranged around a bay like its sister city in Italy.
</P>
<P>
   The new Islands of Adventure, and CityWalk's
restaurants/shopping/nightclubs will double Universal's size.
</P>
<P>
   Now open at CityWalk is Jimmy Buffett's Margaritaville, the new,
relocated Hard Rock Cafe and concert venue, NASCAR Cafe, Bob Marley
cafe, The Groove nightclub, CityJazz and Pat O'Briens.
</P>
<P>
   Open in April is Motown Cafe, Emeril's Restaurant, Pastamore and
Latin Quarter plus a dozen specialty shops including All-Star
Collectibles (sports), Fossil, Cigarz, Tabasco Country Store and
The Universal Studios Store.
</P>
<P>
   A 20-screen Universal movie theater opens in May and an NBA
restaurant this summer.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
