<P>
   SPORTS-SEXHARASSMENT (Undated) _ In an odd twist, the rise in
reports of harassment by male coaches is acknowledged to be an
unanticipated byproduct of a Title IX, the 1972 law barring sex
discrimination at schools that receive federal money. As
participation in organized women's athletics has greatly increased,
creating a need for thousands of new coaches, the share of those
coaches who are women has dropped. And female athletes, afraid of
losing their spots on teams, rarely report their coaches. By Robin
Finn.
