</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Don't rile Pitino
 &HT;    By Jeffrey Denberg
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Fans in Cleveland learned not to mess with coach Rick
Pitino's young Celtics players.
</P>
<P>
   It happened after Celtics center Eric Riley went up with
Cavaliers center Vitaly Potapenko for a rebound and came down with
a headlock grip. Potapenko, wearing a mask to protect a previously
broken nose, took exception and shoving ensued. Riley was called
for a foul. He and Cavs forward Shawn Kemp were called for a double
technical.
</P>
<P>
   That's when a fan got on Riley and Pitino fired back.
</P>
<P>
   ``Who are you to criticize anyone,'' Pitino said. ``What an
athletic body you've got. Have another beer. ... I can't believe
you're calling somebody else a CBA player. You making fun of
somebody's body? That's a joke.''
</P>
<P>
   CAMBY IN DOGHOUSE
</P>
<P>
   Marcus Camby played himself out of the Knicks' rotation after
Shawn Kemp twice went right over him to score.
</P>
<P>
   Knicks coach Jeff Van Gundy gave Camby another chance in another
game, but he got one basket and one rebound in nine minutes to go
with two blocks. So, the next night against the physical Heat,
Camby sat and watched for the entire game. Next night, he didn't
play again. ... Miami is holding on to Terry Mills, who can't play
because of continued knee problems. The Heat figures his $1.15
million salary may be needed to even a trade, but he's played his
last game for the team.
</P>
<P>
   VAN HORN ON FASHION
</P>
<P>
   About those bizarre new Nets uniforms _ a V-neck jersey
described as cool-metal gray _ New Jersey forward Keith Van Horn
said, ``To tell you the truth, I could care less. I couldn't care
if I was in a tank top and a pair of OP (Ocean Pacific) shorts.
It's just a uniform.'' ... Is this possible? 76ers guard Allen
Iverson's mom, Ann, went to high school with Rick Mahorn, Iverson's
newest teammate.
</P>
<P>
   DALY ON RODMAN
</P>
<P>
   Magic coach Chuck Daly says he never had a chance to be reunited
in Orlando with Lakers forward Dennis Rodman. ``I think he wanted
to go to L.A. all along. I never really thought we had a chance to
get him here. I think he may have started that in order to get some
leverage or something with the Lakers. I think Los Angeles provides
him with just the type of stage that he was looking for.''
</P>
<P>
   Still pro-Rodman, Daly says, ``He can help educate your people
and because he's willing to do it. He'll do all of the rotations;
he'll do all of the dirty work.
</P>
<P>
   ``I love watching Dennis play.''
</P>
<P>
   Krause patient with Floyd
</P>
<P>
   Bulls general manager Jerry Krause says he's pleased with new
coach Tim Floyd: ``General managers generally know what they give a
coach. They know if they give them a 40-win team, a 50-win team. We
gave Phil (Jackson) 60-win teams and he did what he was supposed to
do. We can't give Tim the same kind of team. Our job is to get back
to where we can get Tim the same type of players we gave Phil.''
... Charlotte's Bobby Phills agrees. After losing to the new-look
Bulls, Phills moaned, ``There's no excuse to lose to this Bulls
team.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
