<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-06 16:05 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A0260 &Cx1f; tad-z
u l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-ANOREXIA-COSTLY07-COX     03-06 0344
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ANOREXIA-COSTLY07-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Curing anorexia a costly commitment
 &HT;    EDs: EMBARGOED for Monday, March 8
 &HT;    By Kevin Lamb
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio _ When Bill and Susan Winkler decided to send their
daughter Caroline to the Renfrew Center for treatment of her eating
disorder, they knew it was a $16,000 commitment. They also knew
people with eating disorders often need to return for further
treatment.
