<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ANOREXIA-RESOURCE07-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Resources for fighting eating disorders
 &HT;    By Staff reports
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio _ These groups meet regularly to help people with
eating disorders:
</P>
<P>
   _ The Association of Anorexia Nervosa and Related Disorders
support group is for people with eating disorders and their
families and friends, providing support, education and discussion.
</P>
<P>
   _ Overeaters Anonymous is a 12-step program for people with
eating disorders, including compulsive overeating, anorexia and
bulimia. For information about meetings, call Overeaters Anonymous
Hotline at (800) 589-6262.
</P>
<P>
   OTHER INFORMATION
</P>
<P>
   Web sites and phone numbers for national organizations dealing
with eating disorders:
</P>
<P>
   _ Anorexia Nervosa and Related Eating Disorders (ANRED) is at
www.anred.com and (541) 344-1144.
</P>
<P>
   _ Eating Disorders Awareness and Prevention (EDAP) is at
members.aol.com/edapinc/home.html and (206) 382-3587.
</P>
<P>
   _ National Eating Disorders Organization (NEDO) is at
www.laureate.com/nedointro.html and (918) 481-4076.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Association of Anorexia Nervosa and Associated Disorders
(ANAD) is at (847) 831-3438.
</P>
<P>
   _ The American Anorexia Bulimia Association at www.aabainc.org.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Something Fishy Website on Eating Disorders, recommended
by the Winkler family and the Renfrew Center, is at
www.something-fishy.org.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Renfrew Center, with women's mental health clinics in the
Philadelphia, New York and Miami areas, is at www.renfrew.org and
(800) 736-3739.
</P>
<P>
   _ A book recommended by the Renfrew Center and the Winkler
family is Surviving An Eating Disorder: Strategies for Family and
Friends by Michele Siegel, Judith Brisman and Margo Weinshel
(HarperCollins, $13).
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
