<SLUG> BC-MONTINI-COLUMN-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ONE YEAR WITHOUT `SUNSHINE' 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By E.J. MONTINI  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX _ How's it going? Doris Bailey is asked. It's been a
little over a year, now, hasn't it? &QL; 
``Well,'' she says, taking a deep breath. ``It's been 15 months,
two weeks, three days and, let me see, about 12 hours.''
</P>
<P>
   That's how it's going.
</P>
<P>
   That's how it's gone since early one morning in November 1997.
</P>
