</P>
<P>
   After the football banquet Derrek went out. At about 2 a.m. he
stopped, alone, at a convenience store at 16th Street and Southern.
While there, his girlfriend paged him.
</P>
<P>
   He wasn't looking for any trouble, but he didn't have to be.
This is a place where trouble comes looking for you. Several young
men approached Derrek as he was on the phone.
</P>
<P>
   He told his girlfriend, ``I'm about to get sweated by these
fools.''
</P>
<P>
   There were gunshots. He died instantly.
</P>
<P>
   A week later, 1,500 people crowded into the McClintock High
School auditorium for his funeral. The family was there. Derrek's
father, Robert. His mother. Brothers. Along with friends.
Teammates. Teachers. Coaches.
</P>
<P>
   ``This was a special kid,'' says B.G. Jones, who coaches
junior-varsity football at McClintock. ``Not because he was a
ballplayer, but because he was good. You can see that reflected in
his family.
</P>
<P>
   All the eulogies were like that, many mentioning how Derrek's
constant smile got him the nickname ``Sunshine.''
</P>
<P>
   Police believe the killing was random. Derrek, one officer said,
was in the wrong place at the wrong time. &QL; 
No arrests
</P>
<P>
   Doris says she's talked to a young man who was at the shooting,
and who gave her the names of others. She's passed the information
onto police, but no arrests have been made.
</P>
<P>
   ``The detective in charge has some good information on potential
suspects,'' a police spokesman told me, ``but at this point there's
not enough to arrest anybody.''
</P>
<P>
   The county prosecutor handling the case told me the same thing,
adding, ``It's a very active case.''
</P>
<P>
   Not to Doris, who hopes to meet with police officials in a few
weeks.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's almost like I'm being victimized all over again,'' she
says. ``All this time. It's like my baby has been forgotten. It's
been very, very hard.''
</P>
<P>
   Life is a war in which everyone suffers losses. For most of us,
the enemy is age or illness. Sometimes it's accident. Sometimes _
too often in a city _ the opposition carries guns.
</P>
<P>
   There are more casualties than there is newspaper space to write
about them, and no real reason to choose Derrek over any other _
except maybe for the unusual weather around his mother's house.
</P>
<P>
   Here she is, living in the desert, with no rain for months and
hardly a cloud in the sky, but no sunshine. &QL; 
E.J. Montini can be reached at 444-8978, or at
ed.montini(at)pni.com via e-mail. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
